# 🏗️ Autonomous Structural Intelligence System

An AI-powered floor plan analyzer built for hackathon.

## 🚀 What It Does
- Upload any floor plan image
- Automatically detects rooms, walls, and layout using OpenCV
- Highlights detected structures with color-coded boxes
- Recommends building materials (Brick, Steel, Glass, Concrete, etc.)
- Explains WHY each material is recommended
- Generates downloadable analysis report

## 🛠️ Tech Stack
- Python 3.13
- Streamlit (Web UI)
- OpenCV (Image Processing)
- NumPy (Array Operations)
- Pillow (Image Handling)

## ⚙️ How to Run

### 1. Install Dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

### 2. Run the App
cd structural_intelligence
streamlit run app.py

### 3. Open Browser
Go to: http://localhost:8501

## 📁 Project Structure
structural_intelligence/
├── app.py               # Main Streamlit application
├── requirements.txt     # Dependencies
├── utils/
│   ├── detector.py      # OpenCV image processing
│   └── recommender.py   # Material recommendation logic
└── sample_images/       # Test floor plan images

## 🔍 How It Works
1. User uploads a floor plan image
2. OpenCV converts to grayscale → applies edge detection → finds contours
3. Contours are filtered by area to identify rooms/walls
4. Material recommendations are generated based on detected structure size
5. Results displayed visually with annotated image + material report

